WEBVTT

00:06.257 --> 00:09.260
[Uther] The Kingdom of Kingdoms
has a new heir.

00:09.343 --> 00:11.053
For the honor of becoming
Mordred's protector,

00:11.136 --> 00:13.097
I give you my oath.

00:13.180 --> 00:15.850
[Merlin] Uther's letting his
enemies get too close, Arthur.

00:15.933 --> 00:18.102
I am not coming back.

00:18.185 --> 00:19.854
[gasps and grunts]

00:19.937 --> 00:21.146
[Uther] Look for me

00:21.230 --> 00:23.232
when you cross the water
to the other world.

00:23.315 --> 00:25.442
[flames crackling]

00:25.526 --> 00:27.486
[Norwenna] Welcome to Avalon,
King Gundleus.

00:27.570 --> 00:28.904
Would you honor us
and eat with us?

00:28.988 --> 00:32.199
-A baby cannot rule Britain.
-[screams]

00:32.283 --> 00:33.701
-[Gundleus] Kill them all!
-[Morgan] Run!

00:33.784 --> 00:35.411
[grunting]

00:35.494 --> 00:38.789
-[Gundleus] Druidess...
-[grunts]

00:38.873 --> 00:40.291
Lord!

00:40.374 --> 00:42.001
[Ladwys]
This is not the Edling King.

00:42.084 --> 00:44.920
They've changed the child.

00:45.004 --> 00:47.381
[Gundleus] You were
the mother of a king. Now...

00:47.464 --> 00:49.341
-[knife slices]
-...you're nothing.

00:49.425 --> 00:51.802
[Morgan] Come! Come!
We must move!

00:51.886 --> 00:54.221
Attack!

00:54.305 --> 00:55.763
[Morgan] Form a circle
around the king!

00:55.848 --> 00:57.975
You are a traitor
and a murderer!

00:58.058 --> 00:59.643
Kill him!

01:03.022 --> 01:04.690
Arthur has come.

01:04.773 --> 01:07.192
[dramatic music]

01:09.069 --> 01:12.072
[grim music]

01:12.156 --> 01:14.199
[horse whinnies]

01:20.831 --> 01:24.793
[horses whinnying]

01:29.131 --> 01:31.467
[whinnying]

01:31.550 --> 01:34.386
[horses nickering]

01:42.226 --> 01:43.729
Your sword.

01:45.564 --> 01:47.733
-[whinnies]
-Drop it.

01:50.778 --> 01:53.447
[laughs]

02:41.078 --> 02:41.787
[dramatic music plays]

02:51.046 --> 02:53.465
[bird screeching]

02:57.845 --> 03:00.139
[Bedwin] May I see
the goodness of the Lord

03:00.222 --> 03:02.683
in the land of the living.

03:02.766 --> 03:05.060
May I be strong and take heart

03:05.144 --> 03:07.187
and wait for the Lord.

03:08.147 --> 03:10.274
[Sansum] Bishop Bedwin,
riders are approaching.

03:10.357 --> 03:12.317
Come quickly.

03:14.695 --> 03:17.781
[dramatic horns play]

03:27.082 --> 03:28.834
[Bedwin] It can't be.

03:30.252 --> 03:32.212
Open the gates!

03:32.296 --> 03:35.382
♪♪♪♪♪

03:41.221 --> 03:43.474
Bedwin.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.893
[Mordred fusses]

03:45.976 --> 03:48.020
Arthur!

03:48.103 --> 03:50.606
[Mordred crying]

03:50.688 --> 03:52.775
-[Bedwin] The Edling King.
-[Sansum] Praise be.

03:52.858 --> 03:55.277
The Lord has shown us a miracle,
Bedwin.

03:55.360 --> 03:57.654
This was no miracle.

03:57.738 --> 04:03.160
My sister...
and all these brave souls--

04:03.243 --> 04:04.828
they saved him.

04:04.912 --> 04:05.746
And Gundleus?

04:05.829 --> 04:07.498
-[grunts]
-[whinnies]

04:07.581 --> 04:09.458
-We kill him!
-[Morgan] Yes!

04:09.541 --> 04:13.003
Traitor! You murdered our queen!

04:13.087 --> 04:14.338
And raped our Druidess.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.715
But the gods are still
with her...

04:16.799 --> 04:18.883
-[grunts]
-...and they demand punishment!

04:18.967 --> 04:20.636
You must die!

04:20.719 --> 04:23.055
"I desire mercy, not sacrifice."
This is barbaric beyond--

04:23.138 --> 04:24.723
It's a fitting revenge.

04:24.806 --> 04:28.352
-[grunting]
-[yelling]

04:28.435 --> 04:32.064
Gundleus Ap Meir,

04:32.147 --> 04:34.733
King of Siluria,

04:34.817 --> 04:37.361
the gods rejoice in your death.

04:37.444 --> 04:39.029
-No!
-Ladwys!

04:39.113 --> 04:40.030
[yells]

04:42.282 --> 04:43.867
Unhand me!

04:43.951 --> 04:48.831
I am Merlin's Druidess,
and I demand my sacrifice!

04:48.914 --> 04:52.501
No one is questioning
your status, Nimue,

04:52.584 --> 04:55.420
or your suffering.

04:55.504 --> 04:56.755
[gasps]

04:56.839 --> 05:00.551
There will be
no more blood spilt today.

05:00.634 --> 05:02.427
On his feet.
Remove their armor.

05:02.511 --> 05:04.721
[pants]

05:06.806 --> 05:09.393
-Brother, are you mad?
-Why are you doing this?

05:09.476 --> 05:11.270
Killing Gundleus will not

05:11.353 --> 05:12.688
bring peace to Britain.

05:12.771 --> 05:15.399
It'll bring peace to me.

05:15.482 --> 05:17.067
Where can we keep
the prisoners secure?

05:17.151 --> 05:19.862
Well, there is nowhere.
Uther kept no prisoners.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.363
I prefer sacrifice
to imprisonment.

05:21.446 --> 05:26.076
[Morgan] Arthur...
don't break the way of things.

05:28.495 --> 05:30.205
King's chamber has a lock.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.250
[scoffs]

05:33.333 --> 05:36.336
You'd put this traitor
in our father's chamber?

05:36.420 --> 05:40.215
Trust me... sister.

05:41.884 --> 05:46.263
[crying]

05:46.346 --> 05:50.475
[continues crying]

05:54.229 --> 05:55.397
Arthur.

05:55.480 --> 05:58.483
[Mordred fussing]

06:00.277 --> 06:02.779
You have denied me my peace

06:02.863 --> 06:04.406
and Sulevia,
the Goddess of governance,

06:04.489 --> 06:06.116
her sacrifice.

06:07.826 --> 06:11.205
You will know pain like my pain.

06:11.288 --> 06:13.874
And you will be punished.

06:19.546 --> 06:22.633
[Ladwys grunting]

06:22.716 --> 06:26.845
[Ladwys panting]

06:30.556 --> 06:33.268
Is this where Uther's soul
crossed over to the other world?

06:33.352 --> 06:34.686
It is.

06:34.770 --> 06:36.605
I can't stay here.
I can't stay here!

06:36.688 --> 06:38.315
[Gundleus] Let her go.
She's not harmed you.

06:38.398 --> 06:41.026
[Morgan] Oh, she killed her
share of the people of Avalon.

06:43.111 --> 06:45.113
-[door closes]
-She remains here.

06:45.197 --> 06:47.199
[breathing shakily]

06:47.282 --> 06:48.742
Clear the chamber.

06:48.825 --> 06:50.327
Make sure there's
no means for escape.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.246
[keys jangling]

06:52.329 --> 06:55.165
King Gundleus, we'll bring you
food and water.

06:55.249 --> 06:57.167
[door opens]

06:57.251 --> 06:59.503
So, while we rot,
you steal the kingdom?

06:59.586 --> 07:02.589
Your father smelled you
for a bastard traitor, Arthur.

07:02.673 --> 07:04.383
You stay away
until the old man dies,

07:04.466 --> 07:06.760
and then you seize your chance.

07:06.843 --> 07:08.679
The crippled king's
no safer with him than me.

07:08.762 --> 07:10.097
[chuckles]

07:10.180 --> 07:11.890
Once...

07:13.934 --> 07:15.936
...in front of my father,

07:16.019 --> 07:19.606
I swore that I would guard
any child that he bore.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.904
And I swear it again.

07:28.824 --> 07:31.451
If any man should harm me
the Edling King,

07:31.535 --> 07:34.746
I will revenge that harm.

07:41.670 --> 07:43.755
I will protect his life
with my own.

07:48.552 --> 07:50.887
[door creaks open and closes]

07:57.477 --> 08:00.397
[mysterious music]

08:00.480 --> 08:03.358
♪♪♪♪♪

08:13.451 --> 08:16.496
[crying]

08:16.580 --> 08:19.708
[sobs]

08:27.799 --> 08:29.301
[gasps]

08:29.384 --> 08:31.470
Merlin told me...

08:31.553 --> 08:35.474
the gods are like mist,

08:35.557 --> 08:40.062
drifting, fading.

08:40.145 --> 08:44.274
If we hear them and please them,

08:44.358 --> 08:46.276
then they'll thicken,

08:46.360 --> 08:49.029
and they'll join
to cover all the land.

08:49.112 --> 08:51.448
[sniffles] They'll protect us.

08:51.531 --> 08:53.909
[cries]

08:53.992 --> 08:57.204
But if we deny them, we're lost.

08:57.287 --> 09:00.665
[cries]

09:00.749 --> 09:02.167
I thought Arthur
would understand,

09:02.250 --> 09:06.088
but he doesn't.
He doesn't understand anything.

09:06.171 --> 09:09.758
[crying]

09:13.887 --> 09:15.013
[sniffles]

09:22.312 --> 09:24.731
Do you love me?

09:24.815 --> 09:28.276
[breathing heavily]

09:34.866 --> 09:36.201
[sniffles]

09:37.744 --> 09:38.995
Hold out your palm.

09:55.554 --> 09:58.682
Come Sulis, Belisima,

09:58.765 --> 10:01.393
Nehallenia.

10:01.476 --> 10:02.769
[Derfel gasping]

10:02.853 --> 10:04.646
[panting]

10:04.729 --> 10:06.148
Ollodius,

10:06.231 --> 10:08.525
Nodens, Manawdyn, fab Lyr.

10:08.608 --> 10:09.860
Ahh.

10:09.943 --> 10:10.694
[bird cawing]

10:10.777 --> 10:12.654
[gasps]

10:12.737 --> 10:16.950
[exhaling deeply]

10:20.454 --> 10:24.040
As long as you carry the scar,
your life is mine.

10:24.124 --> 10:27.544
[breathing heavily]

10:27.627 --> 10:29.754
So long as I carry the scar...

10:32.799 --> 10:34.926
[whispers]
...my life is yours.

10:37.804 --> 10:39.431
We're as one, Derfel.

10:50.650 --> 10:53.487
[flames crackling]

10:59.201 --> 11:00.785
[grunts]

11:00.869 --> 11:02.954
-[blade clanks]
-[Bedwin] I'm...

11:03.038 --> 11:07.375
I'm sure we can find room
for you inside Caer Cadarn.

11:07.459 --> 11:09.169
We're used
to sleeping like this.

11:09.252 --> 11:10.545
[chuckles]

11:10.629 --> 11:13.423
That's God's miracle you came.
Kingdoms need kings.

11:13.507 --> 11:15.425
Without them, they're...

11:15.509 --> 11:19.471
they're empty land,
inviting a conqueror's spears.

11:19.554 --> 11:21.223
[clank, water splashes]

11:21.306 --> 11:22.933
[grunts]

11:23.016 --> 11:24.601
[whistles]

11:24.684 --> 11:26.061
[Arthur] Wash time!

11:26.144 --> 11:28.188
[indistinct conversations]

11:28.271 --> 11:31.107
[Bedwin] Arthur. Arthur...

11:31.191 --> 11:33.485
at the end,
your father talked of you.

11:36.488 --> 11:39.366
I believe
he regretted his actions.

11:44.204 --> 11:45.956
[Bedwin] How long will you stay?

11:46.039 --> 11:47.874
[Arthur] For as long
as you need us.

11:49.251 --> 11:53.672
I've counted 15 men defending
the whole of Caer Cadarn.

11:53.755 --> 11:55.131
[whistles]

11:55.215 --> 11:57.968
Lord Owain took most of
our warriors on a war party.

11:59.177 --> 12:01.805
Uther increasingly
relied on him.

12:01.888 --> 12:04.641
He's fighting the Saxons
at Calleva.

12:04.724 --> 12:07.811
The Saxons are in Calleva?

12:07.894 --> 12:09.396
Every spring, more boats come

12:09.479 --> 12:11.481
and more Saxons press west
towards us.

12:11.565 --> 12:14.067
We'll all be Saxons soon,

12:14.150 --> 12:16.653
unless the kingdoms
destroy each other first.

12:16.736 --> 12:17.946
[thud]

12:18.029 --> 12:22.284
-So, nothing's changed, then?
-Arthur...

12:22.367 --> 12:26.538
If anything, it's got worse.

12:26.621 --> 12:29.082
Truly, Britain bleeds.

12:29.165 --> 12:31.751
Think about staying, please.

12:31.835 --> 12:35.630
[dramatic music]

12:38.883 --> 12:42.512
[gentle music]

12:42.596 --> 12:45.223
♪♪♪♪♪

13:02.532 --> 13:04.242
He seems so alert.

13:08.872 --> 13:10.957
Is that normal for his age?

13:11.041 --> 13:13.001
You're asking me?

13:13.084 --> 13:15.128
[chuckles]

13:16.796 --> 13:19.049
I have something for you.

13:25.555 --> 13:28.016
Bear's tooth...

13:28.099 --> 13:30.560
for my fearless sister.

13:34.397 --> 13:37.233
[inhales and exhales deeply]

13:38.234 --> 13:41.363
I thought we were dead.

13:41.446 --> 13:43.782
Sorry, I should
have come sooner.

13:43.865 --> 13:46.743
There's nothing to be sorry for.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.953
You saved us.

13:51.206 --> 13:53.917
I should have done more.

13:54.000 --> 13:57.128
-That day when our father--
-Let's not talk of him.

14:01.716 --> 14:04.469
I'll just say one thing.

14:04.552 --> 14:08.223
If he was alive now,
he'd be so grateful to you.

14:10.684 --> 14:13.019
He was so desperate
to keep Mordred on the throne

14:13.103 --> 14:17.107
that he took
a huge risk with Gundleus...

14:17.190 --> 14:19.150
which didn't pay off.

14:21.820 --> 14:24.030
Why are you keeping him alive,
Arthur?

14:24.114 --> 14:28.326
It's both madness and dangerous.
You know what he's capable of.

14:28.410 --> 14:32.330
I've learned that powerful men
are more useful alive than dead.

14:39.045 --> 14:43.258
[indistinct conversations]

14:53.893 --> 14:55.145
What?

14:55.228 --> 14:57.772
Where are we going
to sleep tonight?

14:57.856 --> 15:01.443
Don't worry about that. Our lord
has found rooms for you.

15:01.526 --> 15:03.319
You'll feel better tomorrow.

15:03.403 --> 15:07.282
However bad a day has been,
the sun rises on the next.

15:07.365 --> 15:09.492
Bo, are you sure about that,
Sag?

15:09.576 --> 15:12.787
Seems to me Britain's a land
of mist and rain.

15:12.871 --> 15:14.998
[Sagramor] And Gaul is not?

15:15.081 --> 15:18.001
Well, I suppose... [chuckles]
I suppose you know better.

15:18.084 --> 15:20.336
Hey. [sniffs] Alors...

15:20.420 --> 15:22.672
who of you knew my lord
when he was a boy?

15:22.756 --> 15:24.758
Huh?

15:24.841 --> 15:27.969
Arthur was often at Avalon.

15:28.052 --> 15:29.679
We all knew him.

15:29.763 --> 15:32.514
My--My father, Hywel,
taught him how to fight.

15:32.599 --> 15:35.935
With a sword's edge
against bales of hay.

15:36.019 --> 15:38.146
Arthur's talked about my father?

15:38.229 --> 15:39.522
Of course.

15:39.606 --> 15:43.026
He likes to tell stories
of growing up in Britain

15:43.109 --> 15:45.361
and of the friends
he left behind.

15:45.445 --> 15:48.323
He never forgets those he loves.

15:49.908 --> 15:52.744
-Has he talked of me?
-What is your name?

15:52.827 --> 15:54.370
Derfel.

15:54.454 --> 15:57.749
Derfel? I don't remember.

16:01.252 --> 16:02.545
-Oh.
-[grunts]

16:02.629 --> 16:04.255
-Oh!
-The death pit boy!

16:04.339 --> 16:05.882
-Oh, it's you! [laughs]
-Is that what he calls me?

16:05.965 --> 16:10.220
[laughs] Hey, we've heard
your story so many times.

16:10.303 --> 16:12.722
Yeah? The one, two...

16:12.806 --> 16:15.099
Oh, God!
I've got a stake in my heart,

16:15.183 --> 16:16.768
and I'm going to die!

16:16.851 --> 16:17.852
[laughter]

16:17.936 --> 16:21.356
Oh! God, I'm dying!
Now I'm not dead!

16:21.439 --> 16:24.484
[indistinct conversations]

16:29.280 --> 16:33.785
Lanval, go north to Powys.

16:33.868 --> 16:36.746
I want to know what Gorfydd
is up to.

16:39.541 --> 16:43.837
In Dumnonia,
this will keep you safe.

16:43.919 --> 16:45.755
It's my father's seal.

16:45.839 --> 16:49.300
Once you get to Powys,
you're in enemy territory.

16:49.384 --> 16:53.346
Hey, be careful.

16:53.428 --> 16:56.474
I mean it. If they find you,
they will kill you.

16:56.558 --> 16:59.269
Oh, they've tried, huh,
but they haven't managed yet.

16:59.351 --> 17:00.602
-[chuckles]
-Mm.

17:00.687 --> 17:02.438
I'll be back before you know it.
I mean it, huh?

17:02.522 --> 17:04.649
You blink, like that,
I'll be back.

17:04.732 --> 17:06.943
-Lanval.
-Huh?

17:07.026 --> 17:08.570
It's that way.

17:08.653 --> 17:12.615
[laughs] It is that way. Okay.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.161
[Arthur] Get some rest, Sag.

17:17.245 --> 17:19.497
Tomorrow I want to show you
Dumnonia.

17:21.082 --> 17:24.085
[indistinct conversations]

17:24.168 --> 17:27.171
[horse nickers]

17:28.882 --> 17:29.966
[horse whinnies]

17:30.049 --> 17:31.718
[shushing] It's okay.

17:33.553 --> 17:35.805
-[horse whinnies]
-Let me help you, Lord.

17:35.889 --> 17:39.350
-[horse whinnies and grunts]
-[man in distance] Hyah!

17:42.061 --> 17:43.313
It's you.

17:43.396 --> 17:46.357
[hooves clopping in background]

17:46.441 --> 17:48.526
Death pit boy.

17:50.194 --> 17:51.362
Yes, Lord.

17:54.032 --> 17:55.992
One... two.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.328
[exhales sharply]

17:58.411 --> 18:00.580
When I said it wouldn't hurt,
I lied.

18:02.582 --> 18:06.794
Here you are,
growing taller than me.

18:06.878 --> 18:09.255
You suit your name.
Sagamore told me. It's Derfel.

18:09.339 --> 18:11.633
It is.

18:11.716 --> 18:14.302
My sister said that you
killed a man... Shh, shh, shh.

18:14.385 --> 18:15.720
...in defense
of the Edling King.

18:15.803 --> 18:19.098
-[horse grunts and whinnies]
-Shh, shh, shh, shh.

18:19.182 --> 18:22.936
That without you, the whole
group may not have lived.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.270
[Derfel] It was Nimue

18:24.354 --> 18:27.023
who gave me the courage
to fight back.

18:27.106 --> 18:28.524
[horse whinnies]

18:28.608 --> 18:32.528
-Gods spoke to her.
-[horse nickers]

18:32.612 --> 18:35.990
I'm glad the gods
have not deserted her,

18:36.074 --> 18:38.493
like she must think I have.

18:38.576 --> 18:41.663
[sacred vocalizing]

18:41.746 --> 18:46.000
♪♪♪♪♪

18:54.133 --> 18:56.844
[whispers] Great gods, see me.

18:59.973 --> 19:03.685
♪♪♪♪♪

19:03.768 --> 19:05.478
Save me.

19:12.819 --> 19:15.738
♪♪♪♪♪

19:20.743 --> 19:21.953
Sirona...

19:25.832 --> 19:27.750
...bless me.

19:27.834 --> 19:29.711
♪♪♪♪♪

19:29.794 --> 19:30.837
Heal me.

19:30.920 --> 19:33.798
♪♪♪♪♪

19:41.931 --> 19:44.976
[ominous music]

19:45.059 --> 19:47.061
♪♪♪♪♪

19:53.818 --> 19:56.738
[panting]

20:08.041 --> 20:11.794
-[horse blusters]
-I hear your friends.

20:11.878 --> 20:17.133
When you brought me to Avalon,
she made me better.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.427
And now you've helped her
escape the Silurian.

20:19.510 --> 20:21.971
It's good to repay debts.

20:22.055 --> 20:24.265
What do you wish for?

20:24.348 --> 20:27.143
[horse blusters]

20:27.226 --> 20:28.644
To be your man.

20:28.728 --> 20:32.482
You know how to use a sword?

20:32.565 --> 20:35.860
I've been learning,
and I'm a good horseman.

20:37.528 --> 20:40.615
Maybe I could ride
into battle with you.

20:40.698 --> 20:43.868
Would you want to kill men?

20:43.951 --> 20:45.953
If there was a good reason
for it.

20:46.037 --> 20:48.790
There often isn't, and you
have to sacrifice much--

20:48.873 --> 20:50.792
friends, family.
-I have no family.

20:50.875 --> 20:52.418
You have to put
your warrior brothers

20:52.502 --> 20:57.215
before everything...
and everyone.

20:57.298 --> 20:59.509
Could you do that, Derfel?

20:59.592 --> 21:04.555
Fighting is... the one thing
that I'm good at.

21:04.639 --> 21:06.682
I know it is.

21:08.059 --> 21:10.978
-[pats horse]
-Come on, then.

21:12.605 --> 21:16.192
-I'll show you.
-[horse nickers]

21:16.275 --> 21:19.487
-We're entirely self-sufficient.
-[man grunting, swords clanking]

21:19.570 --> 21:23.157
We have no slaves. We look
after ourselves when we travel.

21:23.241 --> 21:24.617
I don't encourage marriage.

21:24.700 --> 21:26.202
[swords clanking]

21:26.285 --> 21:30.623
No place for regrets about wives
and children on the battlefield.

21:30.706 --> 21:32.708
Those that do have family
barely see them.

21:32.792 --> 21:35.461
-I'll never have a family.
-You say that now.

21:35.545 --> 21:38.714
No. My path is to be a warrior.

21:38.798 --> 21:41.759
-[swords clanking]
-I have my own sword, Lord.

21:43.678 --> 21:45.054
[men yelling in distance,
swords continue clanking]

21:45.138 --> 21:46.097
Salurian?

21:51.310 --> 21:52.603
Breaks easily.

21:54.772 --> 21:56.274
-[sword clanks]
-Our weapons are made of steel.

21:56.357 --> 21:59.443
My mother was a blacksmith.
I learned from her.

22:01.571 --> 22:03.197
[swords clanking]

22:03.281 --> 22:07.160
If you were to join us, Derfel,
you'd have to forget everything

22:07.243 --> 22:10.454
you've come to understand
about warfare.

22:10.538 --> 22:13.291
We train the mind
as well as the body.

22:13.374 --> 22:15.918
Focus is everything.

22:18.754 --> 22:20.882
A strength of purpose.

22:22.758 --> 22:25.761
[men continue yelling,
swords clanking]

22:28.347 --> 22:31.475
♪♪♪♪♪

22:37.356 --> 22:41.444
[pensive music]

22:41.527 --> 22:44.614
♪♪♪♪♪

22:48.034 --> 22:50.036
Well?

22:50.119 --> 22:52.246
It's more beautiful than Gaul.
Admit it.

22:52.330 --> 22:56.042
I don't notice where I am,
just the people I'm killing.

22:56.125 --> 22:58.169
Is it to be Saxons here?

23:00.588 --> 23:01.964
Maybe.

23:03.591 --> 23:05.301
So, then we're staying?

23:05.384 --> 23:06.260
[Arthur sighs]

23:07.803 --> 23:09.055
I don't know.

23:09.138 --> 23:12.099
You don't know?
You can't not know.

23:12.183 --> 23:15.978
You always know. You just
don't know that you know.

23:16.062 --> 23:19.065
You work on instincts. That's
how you make your decisions.

23:19.148 --> 23:22.026
Your head, it just
needs time to catch up.

23:23.611 --> 23:26.572
[horse whinnies]

23:29.116 --> 23:32.828
[horse nickering]

23:42.129 --> 23:43.965
[Arthur]
Where are you coming from?

23:44.048 --> 23:48.928
Caleeva. Saxons ambushed us,
scores of them.

23:50.471 --> 23:52.181
It was a massacre.

23:54.600 --> 23:58.521
[wheels rattling]

23:58.604 --> 24:01.023
[horse whinnies]

24:01.107 --> 24:04.694
[dramatic music]

24:04.777 --> 24:08.322
♪♪♪♪♪

24:08.406 --> 24:11.450
[indistinct conversations]

24:11.534 --> 24:13.995
♪♪♪♪♪

24:14.078 --> 24:16.163
[grunting]

24:16.247 --> 24:18.207
[indistinct conversations
continue]

24:22.795 --> 24:24.880
-[grunts]
-Let's get some blankets!

24:24.964 --> 24:27.425
We need more rushes
and blankets!

24:27.508 --> 24:29.593
-[grunting continues]
-More rushes and blankets!

24:29.677 --> 24:32.638
-Let's go!
-[indistinct conversations]

24:38.728 --> 24:40.688
[horse whinnies]

24:42.440 --> 24:44.692
Arthur.

24:49.655 --> 24:52.908
At least I think it is.

24:52.992 --> 24:56.162
Look at you.
Where's all that hair gone?

24:56.245 --> 24:57.663
♪♪♪♪♪

24:57.747 --> 25:00.166
[exhales deeply]

25:00.249 --> 25:02.168
♪♪♪♪♪

25:02.251 --> 25:06.005
I mourn your father
every day, Arthur.

25:06.088 --> 25:08.841
At least
he didn't live to see this.

25:08.924 --> 25:10.760
We came at 'em
in the early morning.

25:10.843 --> 25:14.013
Suddenly,
the bastards were behind us.

25:14.096 --> 25:16.640
Didn't even have time
to form a shield wall.

25:19.977 --> 25:23.731
Come on. There's more.

25:23.814 --> 25:25.024
[man coughing in distance]

25:25.107 --> 25:28.152
[indistinct conversations]

25:30.446 --> 25:31.781
[coughing continues]

25:37.119 --> 25:39.246
Thank God you're alive.

25:39.330 --> 25:41.832
Many are not.

25:43.334 --> 25:46.170
Do you think they were warned
we were coming?

25:46.253 --> 25:48.798
No one else knew.
Just Uther, myself.

25:48.881 --> 25:50.633
Did Gundleus know?

25:50.716 --> 25:52.968
That's possible, I suppose.

25:53.052 --> 25:55.596
Has he returned
from Gorfydd yet?

25:55.679 --> 25:57.014
You don't know?

26:00.309 --> 26:02.978
Don't know what?

26:03.062 --> 26:05.439
-Let me at the bastard!
-He's my prisoner, Owain.

26:05.523 --> 26:06.941
I swore an oath.

26:07.024 --> 26:08.943
And I swore an oath
to protect Queen Norwenna

26:09.026 --> 26:11.362
and the Edling King,
if you remember. Where is he?!

26:11.445 --> 26:13.864
I won't stop you
from killing Gundleus.

26:13.948 --> 26:16.992
-Is he in there?
-I couldn't even if I wanted to.

26:17.076 --> 26:18.702
My father placed his faith
in you.

26:18.786 --> 26:20.287
It's not me
that rules this country.

26:20.371 --> 26:22.415
What are you talkin about?
I don't rule Dumnonia.

26:22.498 --> 26:23.749
While Mordred is a child,

26:23.833 --> 26:28.045
you and Bedwin rule
in all but name.

26:28.129 --> 26:29.213
[scoffs]

26:29.296 --> 26:31.507
All I can do
is tell you what I believe.

26:31.590 --> 26:34.677
If you kill Gundleus, you cleave
this country wide open.

26:34.760 --> 26:39.765
Vengeance is the way of things.

26:39.849 --> 26:42.435
Maybe the way of things
has to change.

26:45.771 --> 26:48.482
Think, Owain.

26:48.566 --> 26:51.735
Gorfydd could use Gundleus'
death as an excuse to attack us.

26:51.819 --> 26:53.779
We aren't prepared.

26:57.741 --> 26:58.951
All right.

26:59.034 --> 27:02.830
All right.
We'll save his skin for now.

27:02.913 --> 27:05.374
But there is
no earthly reason why

27:05.458 --> 27:06.876
he should be allowed
to stay in there,

27:06.959 --> 27:10.588
in the King's chamber,
with his woman.

27:11.422 --> 27:14.508
Why don't we imprison Ladwys
elsewhere?

27:14.592 --> 27:17.428
[suspenseful music]

27:21.265 --> 27:23.559
Give me the key.

27:23.642 --> 27:27.021
[footsteps approach]

27:27.104 --> 27:28.439
-Here they come.
-[door unlocking]

27:31.317 --> 27:31.942
[door creaks]

27:32.026 --> 27:35.279
They've come to kill us.

27:40.201 --> 27:41.744
[whispering] I'm not
going to take your life,

27:41.827 --> 27:44.413
not this time,

27:44.497 --> 27:46.749
although I really
would quite like to,

27:46.832 --> 27:49.502
seeing as how you're a killer
of women and children.

27:49.585 --> 27:51.337
Oh, Lord Owain,
always such an entrance.

27:51.420 --> 27:53.088
[exhales]

27:55.633 --> 28:00.346
But I am going to take
something even more precious.

28:00.429 --> 28:01.931
[sighs]

28:05.309 --> 28:08.437
-Yeah.
-Don't touch her.

28:08.521 --> 28:10.773
Don't touch her!

28:10.856 --> 28:12.858
Keep your filthy hands
off of her!

28:12.942 --> 28:14.985
[sighs]

28:17.863 --> 28:19.031
I'll bite your throat out.

28:19.114 --> 28:22.117
[sword clanks]

28:22.201 --> 28:24.328
-[chuckles]
-Is that right?

28:26.622 --> 28:28.958
[snarling]

28:29.041 --> 28:31.585
[growling and snarling]

28:31.669 --> 28:36.048
[laughing]

28:36.131 --> 28:38.008
Do you have healing skills?

28:41.971 --> 28:43.097
Of course.

28:44.890 --> 28:47.351
She can help
with your wounded men.

28:54.233 --> 28:55.359
Morgan will keep her close.

28:55.442 --> 28:57.069
-[metal clanks]
-[exhales]

29:01.031 --> 29:02.533
Tell me about the Saxons.

29:04.076 --> 29:05.160
How far have they
pushed forward?

29:05.244 --> 29:07.538
[exhales] Right. Well...

29:08.914 --> 29:12.001
Well, since you've been gone

29:12.084 --> 29:14.920
pushed on beyond the Thames

29:15.004 --> 29:18.132
to Durobrivis,

29:18.215 --> 29:21.010
Strong Gore in Gwent,

29:21.093 --> 29:22.803
and now Calleva.

29:23.429 --> 29:26.348
These towns are outposts
for them, but still.

29:26.432 --> 29:28.851
It's everything
you predicted, Arthur,

29:28.934 --> 29:32.021
and they are getting closer
to Caer Cadarn and Avalon.

29:32.855 --> 29:34.398
What of the tribe kings?

29:34.481 --> 29:39.111
Right? Well, we're still
at peace with Mark in Kernow.

29:39.194 --> 29:42.072
Cadwys governs Isca for us.

29:42.156 --> 29:45.242
Tewdric of Gwent
remains our closest ally,

29:45.326 --> 29:49.371
and there's peace, just about,
with Eachern in Elmet.

29:49.455 --> 29:51.915
Gorfydd of Powys

29:52.833 --> 29:55.461
is hostile, obviously.

29:55.544 --> 29:59.048
His men raid our borders,
steal our sheep,

29:59.131 --> 30:00.799
and burn our villages.

30:00.883 --> 30:02.384
Gundleus is his war dog,

30:02.468 --> 30:05.429
which is why Uther tried
to break up their alliance.

30:09.016 --> 30:12.561
I sent my man Lanval north

30:12.645 --> 30:15.397
to seek information
about Gorfydd.

30:15.481 --> 30:18.359
[scoffs]

30:18.442 --> 30:21.862
I am so glad
you're here, Arthur.

30:21.945 --> 30:24.490
While Arthur's here,
he should become a Protector

30:24.573 --> 30:26.492
to the Edling King,
don't you think?

30:26.575 --> 30:28.827
We need him and his men.

30:28.911 --> 30:30.037
Would you?

30:30.120 --> 30:32.581
[dramatic music]

30:32.665 --> 30:35.167
If you'll have me.

30:35.250 --> 30:38.420
Only if you'll forgive me,

30:38.504 --> 30:40.673
for leaving you
to be banished alone.

30:40.756 --> 30:43.258
♪ ♪

30:43.342 --> 30:44.927
Nothing to forgive.

30:45.010 --> 30:51.141
♪ ♪

30:52.101 --> 30:55.646
Nimue, I've been
looking for you.

30:55.729 --> 30:57.690
What do you want?

30:57.773 --> 31:00.776
I need your help. Come.

31:00.859 --> 31:03.779
[dramatic music]

31:03.862 --> 31:08.826
♪ ♪

31:08.909 --> 31:11.537
Many of these men are dead.

31:11.620 --> 31:14.415
Speed their souls
across the ocean.

31:15.541 --> 31:19.461
You, out of all of us,
can do it.

31:19.545 --> 31:25.676
♪ ♪

31:26.385 --> 31:29.638
[Sansum] May the Lord who frees
you from your sins

31:29.722 --> 31:31.724
save you and raise you...

31:31.807 --> 31:35.978
♪ ♪

31:36.061 --> 31:37.521
Peace be with you.

31:39.022 --> 31:40.149
Peace be with you.

31:40.232 --> 31:41.984
♪ ♪

31:42.067 --> 31:43.569
God be praised.

31:45.404 --> 31:50.993
[indistinct chatter]

31:51.076 --> 31:52.202
I feel your anguish.

31:52.870 --> 31:55.664
Nimue.

31:55.748 --> 32:00.377
The Lord says:
"We repay evil with blessing."

32:00.461 --> 32:03.714
He tells us to find
forgiveness within us.

32:03.797 --> 32:05.090
Nimue.

32:05.174 --> 32:08.260
Let me help you find
a path to acceptance.

32:08.343 --> 32:09.720
You must leave.

32:14.099 --> 32:16.769
[grunting]

32:16.852 --> 32:19.772
[dramatic music]

32:19.855 --> 32:21.064
♪ ♪

32:21.148 --> 32:22.858
[screams]

32:22.941 --> 32:29.072
♪ ♪

32:30.532 --> 32:32.826
Nimue! Nimue!
What are you doing?

32:33.452 --> 32:36.288
-Taking what's mine.
-[pants]

32:36.371 --> 32:38.290
Gundleus made me wear it.

32:44.922 --> 32:46.840
I'm coming for both of you.

32:47.800 --> 32:49.301
Still living, he'll watch

32:49.384 --> 32:51.929
as I sacrifice his beating heart
to the gods.

32:52.012 --> 32:54.640
♪ ♪

32:54.723 --> 32:57.935
When you close your eyes,
see me.

32:58.018 --> 33:04.107
♪ ♪

33:13.700 --> 33:14.785
Nimue, wait.

33:19.832 --> 33:21.917
What happened to you,

33:22.000 --> 33:23.794
it happens to many women.

33:25.337 --> 33:27.339
I know.
It doesn't make it any easier.

33:27.422 --> 33:30.843
He's severed me from who I am.

33:30.926 --> 33:32.135
I need my revenge.

33:34.179 --> 33:37.891
No.
Arthur's orders are clear.

33:37.975 --> 33:40.435
Nobody must hurt King Gundleus.

33:40.519 --> 33:43.479
[Nimue]
You choose Arthur over me?

33:45.440 --> 33:47.693
I'd prefer to have a spear

33:47.776 --> 33:49.611
pierce my heart
than live like this.

33:49.695 --> 33:51.905
No, no, no.

33:53.365 --> 33:56.159
If you do anything rash,
I can't...

33:58.912 --> 34:01.123
I won't defend you.

34:01.206 --> 34:07.296
♪ ♪

34:13.885 --> 34:15.720
[moans]

34:15.804 --> 34:21.684
[dramatic music]

34:35.407 --> 34:38.702
[continues moaning]

34:42.664 --> 34:45.000
Shh, shh.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.335
Father! [moaning]

34:46.418 --> 34:49.171
You're dreaming, Lunete.
You're dreaming.

34:49.254 --> 34:52.215
Go back to sleep.
Shh.

34:52.299 --> 34:55.344
-[moans]
-Shh, shh, shh.

34:55.427 --> 35:01.516
♪ ♪

35:04.269 --> 35:07.856
[dramatic music]

35:10.067 --> 35:13.445
Where've you been?
I haven't seen you all day.

35:14.154 --> 35:15.238
You have to help me.

35:15.322 --> 35:17.074
♪ ♪

35:17.157 --> 35:18.200
You promised you would.

35:18.283 --> 35:21.370
♪ ♪

35:21.453 --> 35:23.038
You know I would do
anything for you.

35:23.121 --> 35:28.919
♪ ♪

35:29.002 --> 35:30.295
What is it?

35:32.464 --> 35:34.341
Gundleus must die.

35:34.424 --> 35:36.885
[dramatic music]

35:36.969 --> 35:42.849
♪ ♪

35:53.652 --> 35:56.363
Cadwys has
paid no tax for years.

35:56.446 --> 35:57.447
I can't believe it.

35:57.531 --> 35:59.574
He's a cunning bastard,
that one.

35:59.658 --> 36:01.743
Uther just completely
lost interest

36:01.827 --> 36:04.454
in harrying
the chieftains and farmers.

36:04.538 --> 36:06.707
[commotion]

36:06.790 --> 36:08.834
[man] Easy.

36:10.127 --> 36:11.503
Hey.

36:13.463 --> 36:14.423
[Arthur] Hey.

36:14.506 --> 36:17.968
Ah. [chuckles]

36:18.051 --> 36:19.511
I was beginning
to worry about you.

36:19.594 --> 36:22.889
You? How about me?
No, no, you don't do that.

36:22.973 --> 36:25.058
You blink and I'm back.
That's what I said.

36:25.142 --> 36:25.642
Lanval.

36:27.477 --> 36:30.313
So Gorfydd is
fortifying his border towns

36:30.397 --> 36:32.524
between Powys and Dumnonia.

36:32.607 --> 36:34.443
He's doubling
his efforts in his mind.

36:34.526 --> 36:35.652
Now making weapons.

36:38.363 --> 36:41.033
That means a full
scale invasion. [tuts]

36:41.116 --> 36:43.035
So that's it, huh?

36:43.118 --> 36:45.620
Uther dies
and Gorfydd makes his move!

36:47.831 --> 36:49.666
All right.

36:49.750 --> 36:51.501
All right, look,
he won't mobilize his men

36:51.585 --> 36:52.961
until after the harvest is in.

36:53.045 --> 36:54.296
[knocking]

36:54.379 --> 36:55.881
Then the weather
will be against him.

36:55.964 --> 36:58.675
If he's going to invade, then
surely it'll be in the spring.

36:58.759 --> 37:02.763
Right. I'll demand fealty
of Tewdrick, Eachern and Cadwys.

37:02.846 --> 37:05.182
We'll have to get their support.

37:05.265 --> 37:06.391
But subtly.

37:08.477 --> 37:09.394
I beg your pardon?

37:09.478 --> 37:12.230
[dramatic music]

37:12.314 --> 37:13.356
Why don't you talk to them,

37:13.440 --> 37:14.733
rather than give them
an ultimatum?

37:14.816 --> 37:16.777
♪ ♪

37:16.860 --> 37:20.655
If they think it's their idea,
might be likely to fight harder.

37:20.739 --> 37:22.240
We'll call them
to the Edling King's

37:22.324 --> 37:23.241
Naming Ceremony.

37:23.325 --> 37:25.077
♪ ♪

37:25.160 --> 37:26.119
They love a feast.

37:26.203 --> 37:32.084
♪ ♪

37:40.217 --> 37:42.552
Tell the tribe kings the call
to the Naming Ceremony

37:42.636 --> 37:45.013
comes from myself
and Bishop Bedwin.

37:45.097 --> 37:47.557
And Arthur Pendragon.

37:47.641 --> 37:51.019
They'll come from curiosity,
if nothing else.

37:51.103 --> 37:52.729
Yes, my Lords.

37:58.276 --> 38:00.946
I don't know.

38:01.029 --> 38:04.241
I don't know
all this intrigue.

38:04.783 --> 38:06.785
I'd have just made them fight.

38:08.078 --> 38:10.413
Do you think Uther sees us
from the Otherworld,

38:10.497 --> 38:12.833
or whatever
you Christians call it?

38:12.916 --> 38:17.337
We call it heaven.
What are you asking?

38:17.420 --> 38:18.713
Would Uther really
want Arthur to be

38:18.797 --> 38:20.090
the Edling King's protector?

38:21.466 --> 38:23.885
I mean, he never did call him
back in from banishment.

38:23.969 --> 38:26.638
Arthur is Mordred's half brother
and a great warrior.

38:26.721 --> 38:29.224
-We need him.
-Aye, but does he need us?

38:29.307 --> 38:30.767
What do you mean?

38:33.562 --> 38:35.021
Arthur's ambitious.

38:35.981 --> 38:37.357
Always has been.

38:37.440 --> 38:38.775
Because Merlin
bred it into him.

38:38.859 --> 38:40.402
[Bedwin] The two of you
can't be divided.

38:40.485 --> 38:42.362
We can't afford it.

38:42.445 --> 38:44.990
Bishop Bedwin!

38:45.073 --> 38:48.910
-What?
-He's like our Lord,

38:48.994 --> 38:49.744
in the corn on the day
of the Sabbath.

38:49.828 --> 38:51.454
What are you talking about?

38:51.538 --> 38:54.082
Arthur is in the fields.

38:54.666 --> 38:57.252
A warrior in the fields
of the people,

38:57.335 --> 39:00.255
collecting the harvest
to protect us in time of war.

39:00.338 --> 39:03.508
[dramatic music]

39:03.592 --> 39:09.681
♪ ♪

39:23.653 --> 39:24.613
[Owain] What's all this?
What's all this?

39:24.696 --> 39:26.489
What's all this?

39:27.574 --> 39:29.075
Is that it?

39:29.868 --> 39:31.870
It's a bit pathetic.

39:31.953 --> 39:33.788
I could bale double
this amount in half the time.

39:34.539 --> 39:36.249
Just ignore him.

39:40.212 --> 39:41.463
[grunts]

39:41.546 --> 39:46.176
♪ ♪

39:46.259 --> 39:47.636
[Owain] Is this what you
imagined you'd be doing

39:47.719 --> 39:49.221
when you came to Caer Cadarn?

39:50.263 --> 39:51.848
[Derfel] No, Lord.

39:51.932 --> 39:54.100
[Owain] No. Me neither.

39:56.228 --> 39:58.855
He says working with his hands
allows him to think.

40:01.399 --> 40:02.442
It just gives me calluses.

40:02.525 --> 40:03.485
[blows]

40:03.568 --> 40:04.819
♪ ♪

40:04.903 --> 40:06.988
[Derfel]
He makes the work look easy.

40:07.072 --> 40:09.449
Uh...
Not so sure about that.

40:09.532 --> 40:11.660
I want to become
one of his warriors.

40:11.743 --> 40:13.495
♪ ♪

40:13.578 --> 40:16.623
[indistinct chatter]

40:16.706 --> 40:17.958
Has he offered it?

40:18.708 --> 40:21.002
Well, he said
he'd reward me if I--

40:21.086 --> 40:23.046
Well, it's out of the question.
All right?

40:23.129 --> 40:24.339
Who knows how long Arthur
will stay?

40:24.422 --> 40:25.924
And we need you here.
We need all our good men.

40:26.007 --> 40:28.260
No. Absolutely not. No.

40:34.975 --> 40:36.851
All right, listen.
We'll train you up.

40:36.935 --> 40:39.020
I'll train you up myself,
all right?

40:39.104 --> 40:41.106
But no more talk about leaving.
Do you understand me?

40:42.524 --> 40:44.109
Yes, Lord.

40:44.192 --> 40:50.073
♪ ♪

40:55.704 --> 40:57.080
Derfel.

41:00.375 --> 41:01.376
Had enough for one day?

41:01.459 --> 41:07.424
♪ ♪

41:07.966 --> 41:09.968
[people cheering, laughing]

41:19.978 --> 41:21.146
Give me some more of that,
will you Bishop?

41:21.229 --> 41:23.023
I need it after
this day's work. Come on.

41:23.106 --> 41:28.737
♪ ♪

41:35.535 --> 41:36.453
[Bedwin] No, no, no.

41:36.536 --> 41:37.996
Oh, you can have one more.

41:38.079 --> 41:41.041
The amount of time you
Christians spend on your knees.

41:41.124 --> 41:43.918
Doing only the devil
knows what mind...

41:45.003 --> 41:46.963
I'm sure your god won't
disapprove of another, will he?

41:47.756 --> 41:49.924
[Owain]
Yeah, just a slurp.

41:50.008 --> 41:52.844
Oh, a little bit more!
Come on.

41:57.390 --> 41:59.809
You must eat.

41:59.893 --> 42:02.187
Gundleus is in Uther's chamber.

42:02.270 --> 42:03.772
There's only one warrior
who guards the door.

42:03.855 --> 42:06.566
But it's locked.
Arthur must have the key.

42:06.649 --> 42:08.735
Yeah. He wears it
around his neck.

42:08.818 --> 42:09.903
How do you know?

42:12.197 --> 42:14.657
I saw it in the fields today.

42:15.617 --> 42:17.410
So we steal it from him.

42:18.244 --> 42:20.789
I have herbs to make him sleep
and you can give them to him.

42:20.872 --> 42:23.166
Me? Why me?

42:23.249 --> 42:26.127
I can't get close to him, can I?
It has to be you.

42:28.838 --> 42:31.257
[dramatic music]

42:31.341 --> 42:33.051
We've never brought
the harvest in so fast.

42:33.134 --> 42:36.888
The people are inspired
by your example, Arthur.

42:36.971 --> 42:39.391
All these men.

42:41.059 --> 42:45.063
Fodder for war against Powys.

42:45.146 --> 42:47.607
We shouldn't be fighting
each other.

42:47.690 --> 42:48.733
[Bedwin] Nah.

42:48.817 --> 42:54.906
♪ ♪

42:59.369 --> 43:01.371
[door slams shut]

43:14.551 --> 43:15.718
Come to take your pleasure?

43:17.429 --> 43:20.390
Or kill me
like the Druidess threatened?

43:21.933 --> 43:24.686
[liquid pours]

43:24.769 --> 43:30.483
♪ ♪

43:30.567 --> 43:32.360
Don't let her murder my Lord.

43:32.444 --> 43:36.448
I won't let anybody murder
either of you.

43:39.367 --> 43:45.248
♪ ♪

43:45.331 --> 43:47.959
[exhales]

43:52.130 --> 43:54.716
Are you married
to King Gundleus?

43:54.799 --> 43:57.719
Even though you're not
of the blood--

43:57.802 --> 43:59.554
-Who cares about blood?
-Ha.

43:59.637 --> 44:00.763
Not me.

44:00.847 --> 44:02.432
I'd be a fine hypocrite
if I did.

44:08.646 --> 44:10.940
We are betrothed.

44:13.651 --> 44:15.195
And where did you
speak your vows?

44:17.071 --> 44:20.950
He took me to Lleu's Mound
and had his Druid bind us.

44:24.329 --> 44:27.790
But his Uncle Gorfydd
doesn't recognize the bond.

44:29.834 --> 44:36.007
Gorfydd has a daughter, Ceinwyn.

44:36.090 --> 44:40.386
He wants their marriage
to bind Siluria and Powys.

44:40.470 --> 44:42.889
[dramatic music]

44:42.972 --> 44:44.807
Is she beautiful?

44:46.809 --> 44:50.396
She's young.

44:50.480 --> 44:53.107
Gundleus doesn't want
the marriage

44:53.191 --> 44:55.985
and he'd never let me go.

44:59.113 --> 45:01.366
Now I have a question for you.

45:02.951 --> 45:05.870
We burnt Avalon.

45:08.706 --> 45:09.874
Don't you hate us?

45:09.958 --> 45:14.420
♪ ♪

45:14.504 --> 45:18.508
Hate is an emotion
that weakens me.

45:18.591 --> 45:24.514
♪ ♪

45:28.476 --> 45:30.478
I try to banish it.

45:35.650 --> 45:38.194
[door opens, closes]

45:39.112 --> 45:41.364
[Nimue]
Derfel. Derfel.

45:42.156 --> 45:43.658
Put this in Arthur's wine.

45:43.741 --> 45:46.828
[dramatic music]

45:46.911 --> 45:48.121
♪ ♪

45:48.204 --> 45:50.164
Are you sure
this won't harm him?

45:50.248 --> 45:53.084
It'll make him sleep,
that's all.

45:53.167 --> 45:54.377
You take the ring
with the key on it.

45:54.460 --> 45:55.587
I'll do the rest.

45:55.670 --> 45:57.130
♪ ♪

45:57.213 --> 45:59.924
Derfel, what? You tried
to kill Gundleus before.

46:00.008 --> 46:01.843
And you stopped me.

46:01.926 --> 46:02.719
If you've lost your courage--

46:02.802 --> 46:06.180
No, I haven't, Nimue.

46:06.264 --> 46:08.516
I just don't want
to betray Arthur.

46:10.602 --> 46:12.020
It's for me.

46:12.103 --> 46:15.523
♪ ♪

46:15.607 --> 46:17.483
Please, do this for me.

46:17.567 --> 46:23.448
♪ ♪

46:29.996 --> 46:31.831
[Derfel] Do you know
where Arthur is?

46:31.914 --> 46:33.666
He's over there.

46:33.750 --> 46:36.085
-[indistinct chatter]
-[horse neighs]

46:37.629 --> 46:39.422
[Morgan] Try it,
maybe you might win this time.

46:39.505 --> 46:40.548
[Derfel] Lord?

46:40.632 --> 46:42.008
May I talk with you?

46:43.217 --> 46:46.804
Do. Morgan's beating me.

46:46.888 --> 46:49.057
[Morgan]
Derfel, why don't you take over?

46:49.140 --> 46:51.351
Don't let him win.

46:51.434 --> 46:52.810
[Arthur]
Thank you, sister.

46:52.894 --> 46:53.936
[Morgan] Good night.

46:54.020 --> 46:55.271
[Arthur] Good night.

46:57.148 --> 46:59.192
What did you want
to talk to me about?

47:02.320 --> 47:04.781
Lord Owain has said
I must train with him.

47:05.490 --> 47:10.328
Well, I won't fight Owain,
even for you, Derfel.

47:12.955 --> 47:14.832
I'd rather serve you.

47:14.916 --> 47:17.752
[Arthur] He's a great warrior

47:17.835 --> 47:21.589
and he loves war.

47:21.673 --> 47:24.550
I do not.

47:24.634 --> 47:27.387
I'm good at it,
but that's different.

47:27.470 --> 47:29.597
Would you like
some more wine, Lord?

47:29.681 --> 47:31.641
I'll have some water.

47:36.521 --> 47:40.608
[dramatic music]

47:40.692 --> 47:47.156
Last summer, King Ban sent me
to fight against a chieftain.

47:47.240 --> 47:49.784
He was attacking Ban's people
in the hills,

47:49.867 --> 47:53.121
so we went into the chieftain's
flat farmlands.

47:53.204 --> 47:58.167
We burned haystacks
and we killed his people.

48:00.211 --> 48:04.924
We did it
not because we wanted to,

48:05.007 --> 48:07.385
but because it needed
to be done.

48:10.054 --> 48:13.099
And we won.

48:13.182 --> 48:15.518
And that was the end
of the killing.

48:15.601 --> 48:21.524
♪ ♪

48:31.409 --> 48:32.785
Do you really want me
to drink that?

48:34.203 --> 48:36.456
Lord, you--you asked for water.

48:38.166 --> 48:40.668
But should I drink it, Derfel?

48:48.760 --> 48:50.052
No.

48:55.850 --> 49:00.813
Lord, I'm sorry.

49:08.946 --> 49:10.823
How did you know?

49:11.324 --> 49:13.367
[Arthur]
Nimue wants Gundleus dead.

49:13.451 --> 49:15.870
I knew she'd turn
to you for help.

49:15.953 --> 49:18.372
[Derfel] I swore to her.

49:18.456 --> 49:21.709
She's my best friend
and she can't think of anything

49:21.793 --> 49:23.211
except him
and what he did to her.

49:23.294 --> 49:24.754
You don't have to explain.

49:27.006 --> 49:29.258
You'll need this.

49:29.342 --> 49:32.470
[horse neighs]

49:32.553 --> 49:38.434
♪ ♪

49:39.227 --> 49:41.103
Do you have it?

49:44.649 --> 49:46.108
Give me the ring.

49:47.443 --> 49:50.279
-Derfel.
-I couldn't do it to him.

49:52.240 --> 49:53.699
What?

49:53.783 --> 49:55.159
I'm sorry.

49:57.787 --> 49:59.247
You're sorry?

50:02.500 --> 50:05.837
[screams] Why, why?

50:09.924 --> 50:11.843
Stop! Stop!

50:11.926 --> 50:13.386
What has he suffered?

50:16.848 --> 50:18.224
[exhales]

50:18.307 --> 50:22.353
♪ ♪

50:53.009 --> 50:55.011
You.

50:55.094 --> 50:57.638
It's as easy to divide
a country

50:59.015 --> 51:02.685
as it is to cut up this apple.

51:02.768 --> 51:07.481
The hard task

51:07.565 --> 51:09.525
is putting it back together.

51:19.702 --> 51:22.580
What if we traded
peacefully in Britain?

51:27.960 --> 51:29.712
Dumnonia shares its harvest.

51:29.795 --> 51:32.882
In exchange, we take furs
from you, tin from Kernow,

51:32.965 --> 51:34.216
copper from Powys.

51:34.300 --> 51:35.343
Every tribe has equal worth.

51:35.426 --> 51:37.303
This country's never been equal.

51:37.386 --> 51:39.305
Dumnonia demands fealty.

51:39.388 --> 51:42.683
Dumnonia must change its ways.

51:42.767 --> 51:46.979
But this wrangling
between tribe kings has to stop.

51:47.063 --> 51:49.523
We can't just take
what we want when we want.

51:49.607 --> 51:50.650
So, what do you suggest?

51:50.733 --> 51:52.735
[Arthur]
A Council of Kings.

51:58.115 --> 51:59.033
Impossible.

51:59.116 --> 52:02.411
It's essential.

52:02.495 --> 52:04.789
Unless you want your children
to grow up slaves.

52:06.415 --> 52:09.710
The Saxons watch
while we kill each other,

52:13.297 --> 52:15.216
doing their work for them.

52:15.299 --> 52:21.389
♪ ♪

52:22.848 --> 52:25.810
Persuade your uncle to come
to Mordred's Naming Ceremony.

52:26.143 --> 52:28.354
[chuckles]
He'll never come.

52:28.437 --> 52:29.897
Tell him we'll pay double
what my father did

52:29.981 --> 52:32.858
for his copper, and we'll buy
the weapons he's making

52:32.942 --> 52:34.151
to fight the Saxons,
not each other.

52:34.235 --> 52:37.071
He won't travel for days
to honor a puking baby.

52:37.154 --> 52:41.534
♪ ♪

52:41.617 --> 52:46.080
The old ways are broken.

52:46.163 --> 52:48.290
It's time for something new.

52:51.419 --> 52:54.088
If he's not part of the Council,
he'll be completely isolated

52:54.171 --> 52:56.090
and so will you.

52:56.173 --> 52:57.425
Bring him here.

52:57.508 --> 53:03.597
♪ ♪

53:05.016 --> 53:06.726
Where's my woman?

53:06.809 --> 53:08.310
[scoffs]

53:08.394 --> 53:12.940
♪ ♪

53:13.024 --> 53:14.775
Ladwys stays.

53:17.695 --> 53:19.488
And if you don't return
with Gorfydd,

53:26.203 --> 53:27.413
I'll kill her.

53:27.496 --> 53:29.790
♪ ♪

53:39.258 --> 53:40.509
Let him pass.

53:46.849 --> 53:48.851
[sighs]

53:48.934 --> 53:50.019
Do as I say.

53:52.813 --> 53:54.106
[Spearman]
Open the gates!

53:59.236 --> 54:01.739
I misunderstood you.

54:01.822 --> 54:03.908
You're more ambitious
than I thought. Ha!

54:21.217 --> 54:24.386
[exhales]

54:24.470 --> 54:28.516
[steps approaching]

54:40.402 --> 54:44.198
You set him free?

54:44.281 --> 54:47.076
You set Gundleus free?

54:49.328 --> 54:50.579
Is it true?

54:52.581 --> 54:54.083
Arthur?

54:54.166 --> 54:55.835
He'll come back.

54:55.918 --> 54:58.796
For what, Arthur?
The pleasure of our company?

54:58.879 --> 54:59.880
It is a risk worth taking.

54:59.964 --> 55:02.133
We cannot afford
a war with Gorfydd.

55:02.216 --> 55:03.926
You didn't even consult us.

55:07.805 --> 55:10.057
So, this is my responsibility.

55:10.141 --> 55:12.643
If the plan fails, you can both
remain as Mordred's Protectors.

55:12.726 --> 55:14.687
And what about you?

55:17.148 --> 55:18.149
My men and I will leave.

55:23.404 --> 55:26.198
I don't understand you anymore.

55:26.282 --> 55:29.702
I don't understand any of this.

55:29.785 --> 55:34.165
Just doing it your way, huh?
As you always have.

55:34.248 --> 55:39.128
♪ ♪

55:43.674 --> 55:45.050
I need to think.

55:45.134 --> 55:46.802
I'll be back in time
for Mordred's Naming Ceremony.

55:46.886 --> 55:48.095
[Bedwin]
Where are you going?

55:48.179 --> 55:52.099
To collect the tax
Cadwys owes us.

55:52.183 --> 55:53.809
Dumnonia's gonna need it.

55:53.893 --> 55:56.145
We're fighting wars
on two fronts.

55:56.228 --> 56:02.151
[dramatic music]

56:04.862 --> 56:07.573
[Nimue]
He set Gundleus free?

56:10.034 --> 56:15.623
He's broken his bond,
with the gods, with me.

56:18.209 --> 56:19.668
I can't stay here.

56:25.424 --> 56:28.010
Nimue, I'm sorry.

56:32.264 --> 56:33.974
I've lost my path, Derfel.

56:36.352 --> 56:38.854
Derfel!

56:39.313 --> 56:40.689
Saddle your horse.

56:40.773 --> 56:42.608
Where are we going?

56:42.691 --> 56:45.903
Tax collection.
You're my man now.

56:46.445 --> 56:47.821
All right. Let's move!

56:47.905 --> 56:49.573
I wanna make Lindinnis
by nightfall.

56:55.829 --> 56:58.707
I want to come with you.
I can't stay here alone.

57:04.255 --> 57:05.673
Lord!

57:06.006 --> 57:06.966
Can I?

57:07.633 --> 57:11.428
♪ ♪

57:11.512 --> 57:12.513
Come on.

57:12.596 --> 57:13.973
[Owain] Let's go.

57:16.600 --> 57:22.231
♪ ♪

57:47.756 --> 57:50.217
[sighs]

57:50.301 --> 57:56.223
♪ ♪

58:05.107 --> 58:08.736
Your plan better work, brother,

58:08.819 --> 58:10.404
or we're all lost.

58:10.487 --> 58:16.160
[dramatic music]

58:19.496 --> 58:25.377
[upbeat music]

58:25.461 --> 58:27.421
♪ ♪
